I am definitely a fan of Kairosoft and thoroughly enjoyed this game. It was 
a solid experience and nothing about it ever really annoyed me like a lot 
of mobile games do. I definitely recommend it. That being said, it's not my 
favourite Kairosoft game. It felt much more linear than some of their other 
games, which is fine, but I ended up feeling like I didn't really make any 
actual choices. I also had a lot of issues with making a good looking park 
that was also easily navigatable by my customers. Still, all of my issues 
with the game are minor and simply the small things that keep this from 
being a five star game for me personally. If I could I would rank it 4.7, 
but since I can't it just doesn't feel right giving the game a five star 
review by default. In any case, this game did reinforce my love of 
Kairosoft, which is something I'd been hoping for for a while now. I'm glad 
I bought it.
